i=\frac{i^2+1+2i}2=\frac{(i+1)^2}2
\displaystyle\implies i^{\frac12}=\pm\frac{(1+i)}{\sqrt2}
\sqrt{i}=x+iy
x,y
i=(x+iy)^2=x^2-y^2+2xyi
x^2-y^2=0
2xy=1
x=\pm y
x=-y, 1=2xy=2(-y)y\implies y^2=-\frac12
y
\implies y^2\ge0
\implies x=y
1=2xy=2(y)y\implies y^2=\frac12\implies y=\pm\frac1{\sqrt2}
\implies \sqrt i=\pm\left(\frac1{\sqrt2}+i\frac1{\sqrt2}\right)=\pm\frac{1+i}{\sqrt2}
